  "summary": "TPC-H scale-10 is a fact-heavy OLAP workload (60M lineitem fact table dominates). Q1 is scan-only (98% selectivity, 6 output groups), Q6 pure aggregation, Q3 and Q18 are filter-join-agg chains with selective filters creating opportunities for Bloom/semi-join optimization, Q9 is a complex 6-table join. Hardware: 64-core HDD system with AVX-512 support. Key bottlenecks are large fact table scans (parallelism critical) and multi-way joins (join ordering and semi-join optimization critical). Target techniques: thread parallelism (8+ threads per large table scan), vectorized filtering (SIMD), semi-join/Bloom filters for filter selectivity, hash aggregation with pre-sizing, zone maps on date columns."
